The targets were made of the compound 208PbS and
having thicknesses of 84 ug/cm2 and 70 ug/cm2
The material was evaporated onto a 15 ug/cm2 thick
detected using large-area 35.7 x 28.4 cm2 position-
laboratory angles from 10 to 80 degrees in the
forward hemisphere and 95 to 170 degrees in the
The characteristic alpha-decay from ERs was
detected in an annular silicon surface barrier
detector which was placed at a distance of 8 cm from
the target, at a mean angle of 174 degrees.
The long-lived alpha-decays were measured using a
silicon detector placed below the annular detector at
a distance of 0.8 cm from the target, close to the
During analysis the alpha-spectra from the
present measurements were fitted using the
peakfitting program FITEK to obtain the intensities
determined by summing the yields for Ra isotopes, the
small fraction of the cross sections for Rn isotopes
associated with CF and the full fission cross
The said fractions were FCF=88 +/- 2% for 12C and
FCF=97+/-2% for 13C-induced reactions, where FCF is
the ratio of the observed CF cross sections to those
